<br>
There, problem solved, and it honestly wouldn't be that hard to code.<br>
<br>
Now, what would happen if they did that?  Raid gear from level 60s would flow to other level 60s that could make better use of it.  The one BIG complaint I have is there is virtually no way to improve my character's gear that doesn't require 30+ people to raid for several hours to kill mob X.  And when I get said improvement it will be taking the place of another raid item that will now sit in the bank.<br>
<br>
IMO the rampant No Drop implementation is KILLING EQ.  It railroads loot to a fixed character that at a certain point many people feel so bound to their character (and have nothing of 'worth') so as to make anything but casual twinking untenable.  Bored with your RoK full cobalt warrior with a CoF and epics?  Well, give it all to your guild and get some decent stuff for your now raid-level ranger.  Epics are lost, but not a huge matter.  Time to &quot;re-equip&quot;: marginal.  Get some lammies and work on your new epic.  Do so now and that full warlords, Jaelin's katana, GoDS, Erad BP, ST Key, Primal, and almost every other slot sits to waste.  Time to reequip?  Well, unless you are in an unusual guild expect lots of resentment.  And unless you are the GL (or a favorite in a subjective award system) or are taking a class with abundant class-only loot (for your guild) you can expect to be sub-par for quite a long time.  <br>
<br>
RoK BP/Legs are droppable.  Didn't see 'twinks' in them for quite a long time and by that was reasonably widespread it didn't really alter the game.  Those person's who could afford it were generally PLd to 40+ anway, by which time they were great items, but didn't alter the classes abilties to such a degree that it 'broke' the game.  Eventually you level to the limit, farm/camp items, and raid.  If they removed the no drop tag from planes armor would guilds farm the drops for cash/trade?  Doubtful.  It is hard enough to get a guild to want to raid for items to outfit the 'last man'.  By the time that was done the item would not be worth the time of those involved to get. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulocrovik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Locrovik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/27/02 4:17:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15042.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Would Happen if All Items Suddenly Became Tradeable</span><hr size=1> would have to have a level limit on everything.  Not like the one they have now but a real one.  Like you shouldnt even be able to hold onto an item of such great power until your level was sufficient.  then you wouldnt be able to trade for it until you were of level to use it.  <br>
