<br>
I know that the tradeskills people despise the TLC because temper components are trivialed out long before you have the resources to get your smithing to Grand Mastery.<br>
<br>
The simplest way to address this is to put the temper components on harder MoBs, and increase the risk / reward for them.  A level 9 steam elemental in Steamfont drops a swirling mist one out of 10 kills if you are lucky.  Make a level 45 Elemental out there  that drops them a little more often, and some MoBs on the plane of Air drop them even more often.  . .<br>
<br>
The TLC freezes farming in it's tracks, combined with removal of NO DROP, and expanding / adjusting loot tables, would make for a very different game.<br>
<br>
I am a strong beleiver in trivializing easy encounters for the High level players.   I am tired of going someplace to challenge a monster that is appropriate for my level, only to find some 50+ player sitting there killing it in 3 blows everytime it spawns.  As it is, PLing and twinking is necessary, as a character is useless to himself and others until they get to the high level game.   The more Verant makes it easy to skate up to level 50, the more the High level guilds are going to have to deal with people who don't know how to play the game, let alone play their class.<br>
<br>
It is heresy, I suppose, to think the TLC is a good thing, but the only reason I don't play on FV is because my friends are all on Bertoxx.  As much as I would prefer things to be different, I just sigh and accept it as a necessary evil to enjoy spending time with friends.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uislington.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Islington</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 603<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/27/02 7:35:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15042.topic&index=38>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Would Happen if All Items Suddenly Became Tradeable</span><hr size=1> /wave Leif<br>
